Title: Formal Specification of an Embedded Multi-tasking Kernel in Z  
Author: Chakrapani Kaligotla 
Date: December 8, 1995  
Pubnum: CPS814 Term Paper  
Abstract: This report describes in brief a pre-emptive multi-tasking embedded kernel. A specification in the formal language Z is given for the key components such as scheduling, message passing and semaphores. Informal arguments are presented to demonstrate that the specification satisfies certain critical properties and correctly models the expected behavior. The primary contribution of this report is an abstract specification, that is independent of the implementation, showing the application of Z to a real system. 
